<font color="#FF0000">MY THOUGHTS ON RULES</font><br>
<tt>Tue Dec  2 12:41:33 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I would like to see the dialog kept clean.  There is no need for &quot;gutter&quot; language.  I know there are those who feel the need to use certain words that are common to our vocabulary. Since we have a worldwide audience, some of whom are non-English speaking as a primary language, language free of cussing and swearing would be helpful to their understanding.  <br><br>
I would also urge people, when composing a post, to do so on their wordprocessor and then copy it into the post field. This would do two things:<br><br>
--It would allow the person to see it twice, to compose it and edit the thought, before it became a part of the permanent record.  They could even do a spell-check (One of my problems)!<br><br>
--It would give that person a permanent copy of what was written.  Unless on is familiar with HTML, getting a copy off this site is difficult.<br><br>
Some people who think with their keyboard, and in this process sometimes put into words thoughts that might not have been appropriate.  My thought is that if we establish this bit of self-discipline the site would be better off. We need to ask ourselves whether this thought is really what we want to send out for the world to see.<br><br>
To take my own advise, I placed this post in my word processor (WordPerfect), and revised it seven times for sentence structure, spelling, and grammar.  This is a worthwhile undertaking.
